WEBVTT

00:00.185 --> 00:01.819
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on The Borgias...</i>

00:01.819 --> 00:03.854
You are the joy
of my life.

00:03.989 --> 00:05.656
You know that I know
that that isn't true.

00:05.689 --> 00:07.491
How long can we
last like this?

00:07.559 --> 00:08.893
Rumour has it

00:08.960 --> 00:10.828
that there are three in
this marriage, not two!

00:10.896 --> 00:12.596
Do not provoke me, my lord.

00:12.664 --> 00:14.832
He could cause public
scandal, if he...

00:14.866 --> 00:17.635
<i>intimates any</i>
<i>impropriety between us.</i>

00:17.669 --> 00:19.403
<i>We are family;</i>
<i>we love each other.</i>

00:19.504 --> 00:20.805
Where is the scandal?

00:20.872 --> 00:22.473
I would confound this pope.

00:22.507 --> 00:24.308
More than
you have already?

00:24.310 --> 00:26.811
<i>I have the arms,</i>
<i>the cannon, and the castle.</i>

00:26.845 --> 00:28.045
This is our moment.

00:28.113 --> 00:30.047
Catherina Sforza
plots with Naples.

00:30.115 --> 00:31.549
She reinforces
her stronghold.

00:31.650 --> 00:33.150
She requisitions cannon.

00:33.218 --> 00:34.785
She will soon
be impregnable.

00:34.820 --> 00:36.587
You are charged with
my sister's protection.

00:36.655 --> 00:38.422
I would know where she is,
where her husband is

00:38.490 --> 00:40.458
<i>at every hour of every day.</i>

00:40.492 --> 00:42.560
I was prisoner in Naples.

00:42.661 --> 00:44.895
And now I'm
prisoner in Rome.

00:44.963 --> 00:46.497
<i>Cesare Borgia comes and goes</i>

00:46.531 --> 00:47.865
like a ghost in the night.

00:47.899 --> 00:49.467
You know he has the
French King in his pocket

00:49.501 --> 00:51.102
and the French army
at his beck and call,

00:51.169 --> 00:52.736
and nobody knows what
he's going to do next.

00:52.838 --> 00:54.171
You hate him, don't you?

00:54.206 --> 00:55.873
I love my hide more
than I hate him.

00:59.578 --> 01:01.779
<i>Let this be a lesson</i>
<i>to those who would betray me.</i>

01:01.847 --> 01:03.614
<i>As Catherina Sforza gathers</i>
<i>allies to her daily,</i>

01:03.682 --> 01:05.015
<i>the end game will be war.</i>

01:05.050 --> 01:06.317
Give me command!

01:06.384 --> 01:07.985
We share the same aims,
Father.

01:08.019 --> 01:09.954
But what are your aims?
You do not share them with us!

01:10.021 --> 01:11.722
If we weaken now,
they destroy us.

01:11.756 --> 01:13.858
I will carve you
out an empire.

01:13.892 --> 01:15.493
Trust me.

01:15.527 --> 01:17.194
<i>Rome is no longer</i>
<i>the Borgia Pope alone.</i>

01:17.262 --> 01:19.663
Rome is Cesare Borgia also.

01:25.070 --> 01:29.547
[♪]

01:29.547 --> 01:33.547
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Borgias 3x10 ♪ </font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Prince</font>
Original Air Date on June 16, 2013

01:33.572 --> 01:38.572
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==

01:38.572 --> 02:53.193
[♪]

02:59.064 --> 03:02.933
I have no servants
when here in Rome, my lord.

03:02.968 --> 03:05.202
Florence can no
longer afford them.

03:05.237 --> 03:07.905
<i>Ah, democracy,</i>
<i>Senor Machiavelli.</i>

03:07.939 --> 03:09.807
They say it has
its merits.

03:13.211 --> 03:15.212
What would you say

03:15.247 --> 03:17.648
is the perfect crime,
my lord?

03:19.751 --> 03:22.786
The one without a victim?
Hm.

03:22.887 --> 03:24.288
The one without a suspect.

03:25.890 --> 03:28.125
And I have often thought

03:28.193 --> 03:32.429
that whoever killed your
brother remained unsuspected-

03:32.530 --> 03:35.399
but made a suspect
of everybody.

03:35.433 --> 03:38.269
Such a one has committed
the perfect crime.

03:40.739 --> 03:43.540
And such a one may,
one day,

03:43.575 --> 03:45.309
make the
perfect prince.

03:53.918 --> 03:57.554
How can one be a prince
without a principality?

03:57.622 --> 03:59.290
One cannot.

03:59.391 --> 04:00.824
Which is why,
I presume,

04:00.892 --> 04:03.794
you came to talk
to me of Forli.

04:05.930 --> 04:09.433
If Rome moves on Forli,
what would Florence do?

04:09.467 --> 04:11.101
You know well what
Florence will do.

04:11.169 --> 04:13.937
What we always do.
Nothing.

04:13.972 --> 04:17.308
We must cross the borders
of Florence to get there.

04:17.375 --> 04:19.476
Do so then at night.

04:20.577 --> 04:22.346
But armies make noise.

04:22.414 --> 04:24.715
I'll make sure
they move quietly.

04:24.783 --> 04:26.583
No disturbance,
no pillage.

04:26.651 --> 04:30.120
Two armies I have heard.
Double the noise.

04:31.423 --> 04:33.757
Can you keep a secret?

04:33.825 --> 04:35.526
The French Army
is already there

04:35.627 --> 04:37.127
in the Romagna forests.

04:38.263 --> 04:39.697
Well beyond
Florentine borders.

